claim.claim-text:
1. A method of processing correlated keywords, the method comprising:
providing a web page having a first input box and an embedded window object that provides a frame for a second input box and a keyword list container;
receiving a primary keyword inputted by a user into the first input box of the web page;
establishing a link between the embedded window object in the web page and a server and obtaining, from the server via the link, candidate related keywords of the primary keyword;
creating a keyword list to present the candidate related keywords in the web page by the embedded window object;
presenting, in the keyword list container of the frame of the embedded window object in the web page, the keyword list to the user;
obtaining at least one related keyword from the keyword list, wherein the at least one related keyword corresponds to a respective candidate related keyword selected by the user;
adding the at least one related keyword into the second input box of the frame of the embedded window object in the web page; and
presenting, the second input box of the frame of the embedded window object in the web page to the user, wherein
the first input box with the primary keyword therein, the second input box with the at least one related keyword therein and the keyword list container with the candidate related keywords therein are concurrently presented, and
the concurrent presentation further comprises determining whether a number of the at least one related keyword in the second input box being greater than or equal to a predetermined threshold, and closing the keyword list if affirmative.

4. The method as recited in claim 1, wherein the creating the keyword list comprises:
predetermining the keyword list container, which includes one or more related-keyword containers;
receiving a request for opening the keyword list;
obtaining a height value of the keyword list and an offset relative to the first input box based at least in part on the request; and
setting a height of the keyword list container and a position thereof in the web page based at least on the height value of the keyword list and the offset relative to the first input box.

11. An apparatus for processing correlated keywords, the apparatus comprising:
an interface unit that receives a primary keyword inputted by a user in a first input box of a web page displayed to the user;
a splicer unit that forms a spliced uniform resource locator (URL) for requesting candidate related keywords corresponding to the primary keyword based at least on the primary keyword;
an object processor unit comprising a link establisher unit, a list creator unit and a presenter unit, wherein
the link establisher unit establishes a link between an embedded window object in the web page and a server, and obtains the candidate related keywords from the server using the URL,
the list creator unit creates a keyword list through the embedded window object,
the keyword list comprising the candidate related keywords obtained from the server, and
the presenter unit presents the candidate related keywords through the embedded window object;

an acquisition unit that obtains at least one related keyword that corresponds to a respective candidate related keyword selected by the user;
an word adder unit that includes the at least one related keyword obtained by the acquisition unit into a second input box of the web page; and
a display device that displays the keyword list and the first and the second input boxes in the web page to the user, wherein
the first input box with the primary keyword therein, the second input box with the at least one related keyword therein and the candidate related keywords presented in the keyword list are concurrently presented, and
the concurrent presentation further comprises determining whether a number of the at least one related keyword in the second input box being greater than or equal to a predetermined threshold, and closing the keyword list if affirmative.
